<subSubSection id="D9AD6543FFB4FFADD5DF8FC9FF58FB78" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="910836C8FFB4FFADD5DF8FC9FF58FB78" blockId="8.[151,1437,942,1293]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="A3C3EADAFFB4FFADD5DF8FC9FEEEFC35" bold="true" box="[199,324,978,1004]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
This species differs from other congeneric species of the family occurring in the freshwaters of the country (Atlantic) by the following combination of characters: upper jaw with a single row of small teeth [vs. with a band of small teeth in 
<taxonomicName id="56B74D4BFFB4FFADD4AA8800FCFAFBEC" authority="(Cuvier, 1832)" baseAuthorityName="Cuvier" baseAuthorityYear="1832" box="[434,848,1051,1077]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Carangidae" genus="Oligoplites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="palometa">
<emphasis id="A3C3EADAFFB4FFADD4AA8800FD0AFBEC" box="[434,672,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Oligoplites palometa</emphasis>
(Cuvier, 1832)
</taxonomicName>
and two distinct rows of small teeth in 
<taxonomicName id="56B74D4BFFB4FFADD0388800FF48FB81" baseAuthorityName="Bloch &amp; Schneider" baseAuthorityYear="1801" class="Actinopterygii" family="Carangidae" genus="Oligoplites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="saurus">
<emphasis id="A3C3EADAFFB4FFADD0388800FF48FB81" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Oligoplites saurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Bloch &amp; Schneider, 1801]; lower jaw expanded (vs. not expanded in 
<taxonomicName id="56B74D4BFFB4FFADD6F78824FBD2FB80" baseAuthorityName="Cuvier" baseAuthorityYear="1832" box="[1007,1144,1087,1113]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Carangidae" genus="Oligoplites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="palometa">
<emphasis id="A3C3EADAFFB4FFADD6F78824FBD2FB80" box="[1007,1144,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">O. palometa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="56B74D4BFFB4FFADD1B58824FAB0FB81" baseAuthorityName="Bloch &amp; Schneider" baseAuthorityYear="1801" box="[1197,1306,1087,1113]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Carangidae" genus="Oligoplites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="saurus">
<emphasis id="A3C3EADAFFB4FFADD1B58824FAB0FB81" box="[1197,1306,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">O. saurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); lower gill rakers 17–20 (vs. 
<quantity id="564F9B2DFFB4FFADD47B8878FE6CFBA4" box="[355,454,1123,1149]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.175" metricValueMax="3.556" metricValueMin="2.794" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="in" value="12.5" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="11.0">11–14 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="56B74D4BFFB4FFADD4D68878FDF3FBA4" baseAuthorityName="Cuvier" baseAuthorityYear="1832" box="[462,601,1123,1149]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Carangidae" genus="Oligoplites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="palometa">
<emphasis id="A3C3EADAFFB4FFADD4D68878FDF3FBA4" box="[462,601,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">O. palometa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<quantity id="564F9B2DFFB4FFADD78A8878FD5CFBA4" box="[658,758,1123,1149]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.683" metricValueMax="4.064" metricValueMin="3.302" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="in" value="14.5" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="13.0">13–16 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="56B74D4BFFB4FFADD7E58878FCC6FBA5" baseAuthorityName="Bloch &amp; Schneider" baseAuthorityYear="1801" box="[765,876,1123,1149]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Carangidae" genus="Oligoplites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="saurus">
<emphasis id="A3C3EADAFFB4FFADD7E58878FCC6FBA5" box="[765,876,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">O. saurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); and first dorsal fin with four spines (vs. 
<quantity id="564F9B2DFFB4FFADD0558879FAD3FBA4" box="[1357,1401,1122,1149]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.27" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="in" value="5.0">5 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="56B74D4BFFB4FFADD0998878FF48FB79" baseAuthorityName="Bloch &amp; Schneider" baseAuthorityYear="1801" class="Actinopterygii" family="Carangidae" genus="Oligoplites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="saurus">
<emphasis id="A3C3EADAFFB4FFADD0998878FF48FB79" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">O. saurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
