<subSubSection id="D9AD6543FFB4FFADD47988D4FBBBFAD4" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="910836C8FFB4FFADD47988D4FBBBFAD4" blockId="8.[151,1437,942,1293]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="A3C3EADAFFB4FFADD47988D4FE72FB30" bold="true" box="[353,472,1231,1257]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Remarks:</emphasis>
This species inhabits estuarine areas and coastal environs; it could be considered as an opportunistic visitor of freshwater ecosystems (
<bibRefCitation id="F5264B39FFB4FFADD7B288E8FBACFAD4" author="Robertson, D. R. &amp; Van Tassell, J." box="[682,1030,1267,1293]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refId="ref66304" refString="Robertson, D. R. &amp; Van Tassell, J. (2019) Shorefishes of the Greater Caribbean: online information system. Version 2.0 Smithsonian Tropical Research Institute, Balboa, Panama. Available from: https: // biogeodb. stri. si. edu / caribbean / en / pages (accessed 27 August 2021)." type="url" year="2019">Robertson &amp; Van Tassell 2019</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
